column1: The supply chain of our organization can maintain a stable state for a long time before any disruption occurs.
column2: Regardless of any disruptions, our supply chain can perform its functions for a long period, and we get enough time to take corrective action
column3: The supply chain of our firm can successfully perform in a wide range of conditions, such as a rapid shift in product demand, or varying production timelines
column4: To address the needs of our customers, our organization has a multi-skilled team
column5: In response to a sudden market change or disruption, our organization can successfully reorganize supply chain resources quickly
column6: Our organization is not critically dependent on a single supplier
column7: To reduce the risk of a supply breakdown in a specific area, our organization choose suppliers from multiple locations
column8: In case of disruption, our organization always keeps a backup plan for raw materials, and spare parts
column9: Our organization always keeps an inventory of finished products to improve responsiveness against changing market needs
column10: Our organization has successfully developed collaboration with all supply chain partners for the smooth flow of goods and information
column11: Our organization collects data from suppliers and customers and exchanges the information with entire supply network members on regular basis
column12: Our organization has ability to quickly sense the major threats in its environment
column13: Our organization prepares alternate strategies for logistical issues such as transportation difficulties, road conditions, and fleet utilization based on previous supply chain disruption experiences
column14: Based on the previous supply chain disruption experiences, our organization develops a plan to deal with the effects of natural disasters such as floods, earthquakes, and pandemics
column15: Based on previous supply chain disruption experiences, our organization devises a plan to deal with disruptions caused by man-made disasters such as labor strikes, terrorism, sabotage, hacking, fire, changes in government policies, etc.
column16: Our organization has the capability for a quick recovery to normalize operations after any type of disruption in the supply chain.
column17: In our organization, we regularly identify and classify the potential supply chain risk during the risk analysis process
column18: In our organization, we analyze the possible impacts of supply chain risks
column19: In our organization, we evaluate the chances of occurrence of supply chain risks
column20: In our organization, we evaluate the effectiveness of possible reaction strategies for identified supply chain risks
column21: Our organization has access to all valuable resources available in the market like knowledge, skills & technologies, through its healthy business relationships
column22: Our organization has developed satisfactory “information sharing platforms” within the firm and with all supply chain partners
column23: Our organization has the ability to collect, combine and integrate data from multiple sources for effective decision-making in the supply chain
column24: To improve the supply chain process, our organization uses advanced analytical techniques (e.g., simulation, optimization, and regression).
column25: Our organization uses data visualization techniques for a better understanding of complex information
column26: In our organization, Information is widely shared with front-line employees so that individuals who make decisions or perform tasks have access to all available data.
column27: Managers in our organization can understand and evaluate the output obtained from massive data
column28: Our organization’s management can forecast the future business needs of functional managers, suppliers, and customers using supply chain data
column29: Our data analytics team has the ability to analyze the supply chain data efficiently that can be used for effective decision-making.
column30: Data-driven decision-making is part of our organization’s culture.
column31: Employees in our organization are always flexible to change their viewpoint based on the findings of the data.

column33: Our organization's profit has been increased significantly during the last three years.
column34: Energy consumption performance of supply chain of our organization and its major suppliers has been improved.

column36: Our organization's supply chain has increased its level of compliance with environmental standards (local policies & ISO standards).
column37: Our organization and its suppliers have taken necessary precautions to avoid solid waste discharge
column38: Our organization and its suppliers' environmental performance has improved in terms of air pollution reduction
column39: Our organization and its suppliers' environmental performance has increased in terms of water conservation.

column41: Our organization and its suppliers place health and safety of all employees on high priority

column44: Our organization and its suppliers pay significant attention to acting against corruption and the violation of human rights (e.g., discrimination, forced & child labor)
